Tautomerism and atropisomerism in free-base (meso)-strapped porphyrins: static and dynamic aspects.
We report herein some outstanding examples of atropisomerism and tautomerism in five (meso-)strapped porphyrins. Porphyrins S0-S4 have been synthesised, characterised and studied in detail by spectroscopic and spectrometric techniques, and their isomeric purity verified by HPLC analysis. In particular, they exhibit perfectly well-defined NMR spectra that display distinct patterns depending on their average symmetry at room temperature: C2v , D2d , C2h , C2v , and D2h for S0-S4, respectively. NH tautomerism was evidenced by variable-low-temperature (1) H NMR experiments in [D2 ]dichloromethane performed on S0 (Δ${G{{{
